****---Main Scripts---*****

FilePortATC.sh is a driver script that automates the process of running compression and cleanup scripts with different JSON configurations. 
The script scans the configs folder for all JSON files and allows specifying which config or configs to use via command line arguments.

Usage

Command Line Arguments

- -a: Process all JSON configuration files in the configs folder.
- -c: Process specified JSON configuration files (comma-separated).

FilePortTakeOff.sh is the driver script that uses rsync to perform incremental backups and upload them to a remote server.

****---Example JSON Configuration Files---****

Main Configuration File (main_config.json)

{
    "server_name": "ServerName",
    "log_folder": "/FilePort/Hangar/Logs",
    "log_file_name": "DefaultName.log",
    "log_keep_days": 1096
}

Directories Configuration File (default_directories.json)

{
    "RunWay_Folder": "/FilePort/RunWay",
    "backup_file_name": "BackupFileName",
    "directories": [
        "/Path/To/Backup/Target_0",
        "/Path/To/Backup/Target_1",
        "/Path/To/Backup/Target_2"
    ]
}

Remote Server Rsync Configuration File (default_clearance.json)

{
    "local_user": "your_local_user",
    "ssl_cert_path": "/path/to/your/cert",
    "remote_user": "your_remote_user",
    "remote_host": "your_remote_host",
    "port": 22,
    "directories": [
        {
            "local": "/path/to/local/dir1",
            "remote": "/path/to/remote/dir1"
        },
        {
            "local": "/path/to/local/dir2",
            "remote": "/path/to/remote/dir2"
        }
        // Add more directories as needed
    ]
}

****---Example Flight Plan---****

Flight101.sh

#!/bin/bash
# Call Compression Script With default_directories.json
# Specify Which Directories You Wish To Compress
#If you do not need compression, you can comment this out
/FilePort/Hangar/Scripts/FilePortATC.sh -c default_directories.json

# You Can Specify More Flight Plans Delimited By Commas
#/FilePort/Hangar/Scripts/FilePortATC.sh -c default_directories.json,default_directories2.json


# Configure Remote Server With default_clearance.json
# You can specify directories that do not need to be compressed, but still need to be synced here
# You must also make sure that the config includes the directory of your compressed files for them to by synced
/FilePort/Hangar/Scripts/FilePortTakeOff.sh default_clearance.json

#After Making Sure This Works, Set This FlightPlan To Be Run By Cron

****---Notes---****

- Ensure that jq is installed on your system to parse the JSON configuration files.
- Make sure the scripts are executable:

    chmod +x /FlightPlan101.sh

- Run the driver script with the appropriate command line arguments to process the configurations.
